Case 209 is an imported case involving a 32 year-old female Singapore Citizen who had been in the United States from 2 March to 7 March. She is currently warded in an isolation room at SGH.

She reported onset of symptoms on 11 March, and had sought treatment at SGHâ€™s staff clinic on 13 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 14 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she had gone to work as a Psychologist at SGH. She stays at Serangoon Avenue 3.
